title: Four Presumed Dead in California Marine Helicopter Crash

locations.name: california marine helicopter crash san diego

text:
SAN DIEGOâ€”A Marine helicopter crashed during a Southern California training mission and all four crew members were believed killed, the military said.
The CH-53E Super Stallion went down shortly after 2:30 p.m. Tuesday near El Centro, a few miles from the U.S.-Mexico border. The helicopter was with the 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing out of the Miramar air station in San Diego, according to a base press statement.
